Sentencas: Ta5+ and W6+ co-doped perovskite SrTa0.1W0.1Fe0.8O3-delta (STWF) is studied as a novel cathode material of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Characterization of Ta/W co-doped SrFeO3-δ perovskite as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The synergistic effects of Ta/W co-doping on the crystal structure, thermal, electrical and electrochemical properties of STWF were investigated systematically.
Titulo: Characterization of Ta/W co-doped SrFeO3-δ perovskite as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ta/W co-doping increased the concentration of oxygen vacancy in STWF, leading to the increase of thermal expansion coefficients (TECs) and electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Characterization of Ta/W co-doped SrFeO3-δ perovskite as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average TEC of STWF is 19.8 x 10(-6) K-1 during 30-1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Characterization of Ta/W co-doped SrFeO3-δ perovskite as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the area specific resistance (ASR) and the maximum power density are 0.074 Omega cm(2) and 967 mW cm(-2) for STWF cathode based on La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.1O3 (LSGM) electrolyte.
Titulo: Characterization of Ta/W co-doped SrFeO3-δ perovskite as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results reveal that high stable valence elements Ta5+ and W6+ co-doped STWF is a good cathode candidate for SOFC.
Titulo: Characterization of Ta/W co-doped SrFeO3-δ perovskite as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
